The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem, and proposes deep transfer learning models to address the data sparsity problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning and dropout strategies, which are related to machine learning, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely. The paper also mentions the use of co-training, which is a semi-supervised learning technique, hence cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with image classification and verification, which are related to information retrieval, hence cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category.
